  "title": "Electronic Equipment Technician (VEP / Checkpoint Systems) | 4 days / Rotating Shift [0580]",
  "description": "<ul><li>2 years contract, renewable</li><li>4 days, 12 hours AM/PM rotating shift (8-8)</li><li>Salary: Basic $2000 + $50 HP allowance + $220 Attendance allowance + OT</li><li>Location: Woodlands Checkpoint x 4; Tuas Checkpoint x 2</li></ul><p><u><strong>Job scope:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Identification, maintenance and replacement of electronic equipment and computers.</li><li>Liaise with government agency on return and collection of faulty or repaired equipment.</li><li>Tracking and recording the fault patterns and trends for monthly progress reporting to government agency.</li><li>Provide guidance to general public on the use of on-site equipment such as Fee Collection Terminals.</li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirements: </strong></u></p><ul><li>Possess certificate in NITEC/Electrical/Electronic or related discipline</li><li>Able to work rotating shifts (4 day work week)</li><li>Training will be provided</li></ul><p><br />The Supreme HR Advisory Pte. Ltd || 14C7279</p><p>Chua Jie Ying (Cai Jie Ying), Evelynn || EA Personnel License R24120580</p>",
